All Classes

Class Description
CheckersApp
The main application class for the Checkers game.
CheckersButton
This class handles the logic for a button on the main menu.
CheckersButton.ButtonSizes
Enum class for the available sizes of the button
CheckersScene
A utility class to represent a Scene, ensuring we have the same global configurations for all Scene's.
CheckersSubScene
Parent class for each sub-scene, creating a layout for all subscenes in the game.
Configs
A global configuration file.
GameScene
Scene handler for the game play itself.
HighScoresSubScene
Subscene to handle the view for the high scores menu.
HowToPlaySubScene
Subscene for the How To Play screen in the Main Menu.
JsonFileIO
Handle the saving and retrieving of high scores utilizing a JSON file format.
Main
The main entry point for the application.
MainMenuSubScene
The main-menu sub-scene in the MenuScene.
MenuScene
This scene handles each of the views for the pre-game menu, including: - Main Menu - Difficulty Selection - High Scores - How to play
NewGameSubScene
The sub-scene for the New Game screen to select difficulty, Player vs Player, etc.
SceneManager
The Scene Manager class manages each of the scenes in the game.
Scenes
Utility class to show all of the available Scene's to segue to.
SubScenes
Utility Enum to list all of the available subscenes in the game.
